0:07:47.040,0:07:50.560
He responded by also making his way to the church.

0:07:50.560,0:07:55.740
The following Sunday, they came out to share their heart-rendering experience.

0:07:55.740,0:07:57.440
Let's listen to them.

0:07:57.440,0:07:59.160
My name is Christie Pua.

0:07:59.160,0:08:00.940
I'm from Indonesia.

0:08:00.940,0:08:03.360
I'm 37 years old.

0:08:03.360,0:08:10.120
These are my children, Frederick and Blessing; he is 13 years old and she is 5 years old.

0:08:10.120,0:08:15.300
The man standing beside them is John Kennedy Egesi, my husband.

0:08:15.300,0:08:24.260
I met my husband in Indonesia about 16 years ago, when he was doing business in my country.

0:08:24.260,0:08:27.960
Since then, we have been married.

0:08:27.960,0:08:35.420
My son Frederick was born in Jakarta (Indonesia) and this one was born in Pakistan.

0:08:35.420,0:08:45.640
After some years of our marriage, my husband decided to bring us to Nigeria to meet his parents.

0:08:45.640,0:08:52.700
I didn't know that on our coming to Nigeria everything would just turn around.

0:08:52.700,0:08:59.280
Nothing worked for us to the extent that we began to suffer greatly.

0:08:59.280,0:09:05.160
I never imagined that we would suffer so much in Nigeria; it was too much for me.

0:09:05.160,0:09:12.360
Even every day I had to cook with firewood, so I had to fetch wood from around the compound.

0:09:12.360,0:09:20.840
If that was not enough, the remaining wood I would give to my son to sell, to get money.

0:09:20.840,0:09:30.260
She said, ever since then she had never expected this kind of difficulties that she, her children and husband

0:09:30.260,0:09:32.700
have been going through.

0:09:32.700,0:09:36.900
Because of these terrible difficulties they have been going through, every morning she had to go to the bush

0:09:36.900,0:09:42.600
to fetch firewood, and after fetching the firewood she was giving some of it to her son to go around the street

0:09:42.600,0:09:46.700
to try to sell it, in order to make money for them to meet their daily needs.

0:09:46.700,0:09:54.020
Not only firewood, when it was the season for aboli, I would pick it around the compound.

0:09:54.020,0:10:03.480
I would clean it, then send my son to take it to sell at the market or if there was eko,

0:10:03.480,0:10:08.840
I would clean it and send him to sell it in the marker.

0:10:08.840,0:10:14.440
All the things I did were to help feed me and my children.

0:10:14.440,0:10:28.980
It's not only me who suffered but my son, he would go to dustbins to pick bottles and things for him to sell

0:10:28.980,0:10:32.260
to help me – to earn a small amount of money from it.

0:10:32.260,0:10:36.200
They dropped out of school for a long time.

0:10:36.200,0:10:42.340
For us to even eat was very difficult, talk less of taking them to school.

0:10:42.340,0:10:48.580
As if all the suffering I went through, for me past five years in Nigeria, was not enough;

0:10:48.580,0:10:54.240
our condition continued to get worse as time went on.

0:10:54.240,0:11:00.800
When my father-in-law died, they accused my husband that he killed my father-in-law.

0:11:00.800,0:11:11.200
After a few months, the niece died and they also accused my husband that he killed the niece as well.

0:11:11.200,0:11:17.640
Before, it was sad but now things have become more tough again, tougher than before.

0:11:17.640,0:11:22.440
After everything that has happened, I cannot bear it again.

0:11:22.440,0:11:26.820
I would plead with my husband every day,

0:11:26.820,0:11:31.980
“Please, I don’t want to lose our lives in this village, I want to live.

0:11:31.980,0:11:36.540
I have left my county for so many years, I still have my family there.

0:11:36.540,0:11:39.240
I don’t want to return only by name.

0:11:39.240,0:11:43.640
It’s better we secure our lives, anything we gather we can sell it.”

0:11:43.640,0:11:52.180
We sold our television and generator for us to get transport to come to Lagos to secure our lives.

0:11:52.180,0:11:54.400
That is why we are here in Lagos.

0:11:54.400,0:12:00.700
We suffered and ran from the village, when we reached Lagos, we still suffered.

0:12:00.700,0:12:06.420
That is what made us to come to The SCOAN to look for help from the man of God.

0:12:06.420,0:12:08.220
Please, man of God.

0:12:08.220,0:12:10.960
Man of God help me and my family.

0:12:10.960,0:12:14.920
I want to go back to my country; I don’t want to live in Nigeria any more.

0:12:14.920,0:12:18.360
Five years is enough for me, please man of God.

0:12:18.360,0:12:20.700
How can I continue living like this?

0:12:20.700,0:12:23.800
I don’t want to and I cannot.

0:12:23.800,0:12:29.200
Even the clothes that I and my children are wearing, someone gave them to us.

0:12:29.200,0:12:34.680
Think about that kind of life – I don’t want it, please man of God.

0:12:34.680,0:12:41.200
There was a clip to show how she was suffering; she was going to the bush, gathering some firewood

0:12:41.200,0:12:42.520
in order to cook for her family.

0:12:42.520,0:12:45.080
Yet, the suffering still continued.

0:12:45.080,0:12:53.380
Since we arrived in Lagos my husband tried to hustle and would go out every morning,

0:12:53.380,0:12:57.200
hustling to get money for us to eat.

0:12:57.200,0:13:04.420
But after much effort my husband would return with only 100 or 200 at the highest 500 naira.

0:13:04.420,0:13:11.080
What can we use that money for when we need to eat and pay for accommodation?

0:13:11.080,0:13:16.520
My name is Frederick, this is my mother, sister and my father.

0:13:16.520,0:13:22.680
Since the day we came to Nigeria we have been suffering – all the time.

0:13:22.680,0:13:28.960
To the extent that I would go to the bush to pick things to sell.

0:13:28.960,0:13:39.280
Bottles and other things just to help my mother.

0:13:39.280,0:13:47.460
I’m not going to school, even my sister is not going to school; we have dropped out for a long time.

0:13:47.460,0:13:53.360
I want the man of God to help us so we can leave this country, we have suffered a lot.

0:13:53.360,0:13:55.460
Please man of God, help us.

0:13:55.460,0:13:59.160
My name is John Kennedy Egasi

0:13:59.160,0:14:01.760
I am from Imo State, Nigeria.

0:14:01.760,0:14:08.440
The people beside me are my wife, son and little daughter.

0:14:08.440,0:14:15.260
We lived abroad for a long time but after some time, I decided to bring my family home.

0:14:15.260,0:14:21.880
I brought them home, everything was fine before I came home.

0:14:21.880,0:14:26.580
But all of a sudden, when I came home everything turned around.

0:14:26.580,0:14:34.940
Things started going bad; nothing was working out.

0:14:34.940,0:14:43.280
Even to the extent that they accused me of killing my father who we had been taking care of.

0:14:43.280,0:14:45.240
How can I kill my father?

0:14:45.240,0:14:51.260
They accused me and started calling me names and all sorts.

0:14:51.260,0:14:58.740
When the insults became too much – we couldn’t take it anymore, we decided to come to Lagos.

0:14:58.740,0:15:06.700
We sold our generator, television and things to get to Lagos.

0:15:06.700,0:15:17.000
When we got to Lagos, we tried to find a place to stay that would cost little like 1,500 naira.

0:15:17.000,0:15:23.260
We stayed there paying 1,500 naira everyday but things got worse and worse.

0:15:23.260,0:15:30.360
I decided to be going out to hustle, to help people doing business or something like that.

0:15:30.360,0:15:33.180
Along the line, still nothing was working out.

0:15:33.180,0:15:41.480
When I would finish work, after working hard they would give me 200, 500 at the highest 1,000 naira.

0:15:41.480,0:15:45.360
I was not able to pay for the house rent again.

0:15:45.360,0:15:48.820
Even sometimes, we would sleep without eating.

0:15:48.820,0:15:55.800
Everything was upside down, it has been too stressful on my side.

0:15:55.800,0:16:06.680
On Friday, I was trying to get home, I was walking on foot because I can’t always afford the bus -

0:16:06.680,0:16:09.920
sometimes when I enter the bus, they push me down.

0:16:09.920,0:16:21.060
I was trying to get home on foot when I got a call around 12 o’clock.

0:16:21.060,0:16:25.840
It was an evangelist calling me from The SCOAN.

0:16:25.840,0:16:27.060
I asked what the problem was.

0:16:27.060,0:16:30.820
They said they had found my wife and kids at their street.

0:16:30.820,0:16:31.920
I asked what had happened.

0:16:31.920,0:16:34.580
They said they were crying, saying they had not been eating and no one knows.

0:16:34.580,0:16:38.080
I shed tears and from there, I managed to get to this place.

0:16:38.080,0:16:45.520
I want to first of all thank the man of God for taking care of my wife from that Friday.

